arsley, & clam juice seasoned with freshly ground pepper for one hour',4,'2017-11-04 01:44:02','2017-11-04 01:44:02'),(30,2,'Cut fish into pieces approximately 2\" x 2\"',4,'2017-11-04 01:44:02','2017-11-04 01:44:02'),(31,3,'Add clams and cook 10 minutes. Add mussels, shrimp & scallops and cook an additional 5 minutes. Add fish and cook 5 minutes.',4,'2017-11-04 01:44:02','2017-11-04 01:44:02'),(32,4,'Serve immediately with french bread.',4,'2017-11-04 01:44:02','2017-11-04 01:44:02'),(33,0,'Combine celery, carrot, green pepper, and onion, in slow-cooking pot. Add broth, butter, and pepper. Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.',8,'2017-11-04 01:53:08','2017-11-04 01:57:39'),(34,1,'Strain mixture. Puree vegetables in blender and return to pot with broth.',8,'2017-11-04 01:57:39','2017-11-04 01:57:39'),(35,2,'Turn control to high. Dissolve flour in small amount of water; add to broth.',8,'2017-11-04 01:57:39','2017-11-04 01:57:39'),(36,3,'Add cheese, 1/2 c at a time, stirring until blended.',8,'2017-11-04 01:57:39','2017-11-04 01:57:39'),(37,4,'Pour in beer. Cover and cook on high for 15 to 20 minutes.',8,'2017-11-04 01:57:39','2017-11-04 01:57:39'),(38,0,'Preheat broiler',9,'2017-11-04 01:58:52','2017-11-04 01:58:52'),(39,1,'Open oysters and leave on the half-shell.',9,'2017-11-04 02:01:18','2017-11-04 02:01:18'),(40,2,'Melt butter with garlic.',9,'2017-11-04 02:01:18','2017-11-04 02:01:18'),(41,3,'Place oysters on baking sheet. Broil for 2 or 3 minutes until lightly browned.',9,'2017-11-04 02:01:18','2017-11-08 16:17:48'),(42,4,'Drizzle garlic-butter over oysters before serving.',9,'2017-11-04 02:01:18','2017-11-04 02:01:18'),(43,0,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees.',10,'2017-11-04 02:13:45','2017-11-04 02:13:45'),(44,1,'Remove clams from their shells, and reserve 16 half shells; Save 1/2 c clam juice',10,'2017-11-04 02:13:45','2017-11-04 02:19:58'),(45,2,'Chop clams very fine and combine in a bowl with onion and parsley.',10,'2017-11-04 02:13:45','2017-11-04 02:19:58'),(46,3,'Mix the 1 T melted butter and bread crumbs; add to clams.',10,'2017-11-04 02:13:45','2017-11-04 02:19:58'),(47,4,'Melt 2 T butter in small saucepan. Add flour and stir over  low heat until well blended.',10,'2017-11-04 02:13:45','2017-11-04 02:19:58'),(48,5,'Pour in clam juice and stir until mixture is smooth.',10,'2017-11-04 02:13:45','2017-11-04 02:19:58'),(49,6,'Gradually blend in half-and-half and continue cooking over low heat for 5 min, until thickened. Add sherry, pepper and paprika.',10,'2017-11-04 02:13:45','2017-11-04 02:19:58'),(50,7,'Thoroughly mix cream sauce in the bowl with the clams. Spoon mixture into clam shells and dot with remaining butter.',10,'2017-11-04 02:13:45','2017-11-04 02:19:58'),(51,8,'Bake until tops of the clams are nicely browned, and 25 min. Garnish with lemon wedges.',10,'2017-11-04 02:13:45','2017-11-04 02:19:58'),(52,0,'Cut shark into 1/2 pound serving pieces',11,'2017-11-04 02:24:58','2017-11-08 01:58:21'),(53,1,'Combine remaining ingredients.',11,'2017-11-04 02:24:58','2017-11-04 02:39:40'),(54,2,'Place shark in single layer in glass dish.',11,'2017-11-04 02:24:58','2017-11-04 02:39:40'),(55,3,'Pour marinade over and marinate fish at least 6 hours in the refrigerator, turning frequently.',11,'2017-11-04 02:24:58','2017-11-04 02:39:40'),(56,4,'Grill steaks over charcoal fire, 5 to 7 minutes on each side, brushing frequently with marinade.',11,'2017-11-04 02:24:58','2017-11-04 02:39:40'),(57,5,'Serve with a dressing of equal parts lemon juice and butter with chopped fresh parsley, or another sauce of your choosing.',11,'2017-11-04 02:24:58','2017-11-04 02:39:40'),(59,0,'Preheat the broiler to full heat',13,'2017-11-04 16:56:16','2017-11-04 16:56:16'),(60,NULL,'Cut the fish fillets into 4 to 6 pieces. Generously butter a baking pan with about 1 T of butter. Sprinkle with pepper. Arrange fish pieces over the pan.',13,'2017-11-04 16:56:16','2017-11-04 16:56:16'),(61,NULL,'Melt the remaining 4 T of butter and stir in the anchovy paste. Brush the tops of the haddock pieces with this mixture.',13,'2017-11-04 16:56:16','2017-11-04 16:56:16'),(62,NULL,'Run the fish under the broiler, about 2 1/2 to 3 inches from the heat source. As the fish cooks, brush it occasionally with more of the butter mixture. Cook 12 to 15 minutes. Serve on a warm platter or serving dish, garnished with lemon wedges and parsley sprigs.',13,'2017-11-04 16:56:16','2017-11-04 16:56:16'),(63,0,'Clean and devein the shrimp. Rinse and drain well.',14,'2017-11-04 17:00:30','2017-11-04 17:00:30'),(64,1,'Add the remaining ingredients to the shrimp and toss to coat evenly and well.',14,'2017-11-04 17:00:30','2017-12-20 20:32:56'),(65,2,'Preheat the broiler to high.',14,'2017-11-04 17:00:30','2017-12-20 20:32:56'),(66,3,'Line a baking dish with foil and arrange the shrimp over it.',14,'2017-11-04 17:00:30','2017-12-20 20:32:56'),(67,4,'Place the shrimp under the broiler about three to four inches from the source of heat. Broil 5 to 6 minutes. It is not necessary to turn the shrimp as the cook. Baste the shrimp and serve hot.',14,'2017-11-04 17:00:30','2017-12-20 20:32:56'),(68,0,'In saucepan, heat olive oil. Saute onion, green pepper, hot pepper, and garlic until vegetables are translucent. Add tomatoes and wine and simmer, uncovered, until slightly reduced, about 15 minutes. Taste and add pepper as you desire.',15,'2017-11-04 17:05:43','2017-11-04 17:05:43'),(69,NULL,'Cut cod into 6 service pieces. Pour a few tablespoons of tomato mixture over bottom of a baking pan large enough to hold cod in a single layer. Lay cod pieces in pan, doubling over thin ends, if necessary. Pour remained of sauce over cod and bake in preheated 350 degree F oven for 15 min.',15,'2017-11-04 17:05:43','2017-11-04 17:05:43'),(70,0,'Select baking pan or skillet in which the dish will fit comfortably. Place small glass bowl in pan. Set dish on bowl. Pour boiling water into baking pan; Cover tightly. Place baking pan on stove and let the water return to boil. Steam the fish for 10 min. Lift cover. If the fish is not properly cooked, re-cover and steam 2 minutes longer.',16,'2017-11-07 19:49:20','2017-11-07 19:54:21'),(71,1,'2 or 3 T of the liquid may be added to any sauce served with fish. Try tomato or mushroom sauce.',16,'2017-11-07 19:49:20','2017-11-07 19:54:21'),(72,0,'Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices. Cut slices into small uniform cubes. There should be 2 c.',17,'2017-11-07 19:53:12','2017-11-07 19:53:12'),(73,1,'Heat half of butter in saucepan & add shallots. Cook, stirring until wilted. Add tomatoes. Cook, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.',17,'2017-11-07 19:53:12','2017-11-07 19:54:31'),(74,2,'Line bowl with sieve and pour in sauce. Press with rubber spatula to extract as much liquid as possible from solids. Discard solids and reheat sauce, swirling in remaining butter.',17,'2017-11-07 19:53:12','2017-11-07 19:54:31'),(75,0,'Rinse mushrooms and pat dry. Cut into thing slices. There should 2 cups.',18,'2017-11-08 00:00:23','2017-11-08 00:00:23'),(76,1,'Heat 3 T of butter in small skillet and add shallots. Cook until wilted. Add mushrooms and sprinkle with pepper. When mushrooms are wilted, add wine and simmer about 3 min.',18,'2017-11-08 00:00:23','2018-03-14 20:31:37'),(77,2,'Put mixture in food processor or blender and blend thoroughly. Return mixture to skillet and bring to simmer. Swirl in remaining butter. Add heavy cream. ',18,'2017-11-08 00:00:23','2018-03-14 20:31:37'),(78,0,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Rinse mushrooms and pat dry. Cut into thin slices. There should be 2 cups.',19,'2017-11-08 00:09:27','2017-11-08 00:09:27'),(79,NULL,'Melt 2 T of the butter in an ovenproof saucepan and cook the onion and garlic, stirring, until translucent. Add the rice and stir briefly over low heat until all the grains are coated with butter. Stir in the broth; add the pepper and bay leaf; add Tabasco to taste. Bring the mixture just to boil, cover and place in the over. Bake for exactly 17 minutes.',19,'2017-11-08 00:09:27','2017-11-08 00:09:27'),(80,NULL,'Melt 2 T butter in a skillet; saute the mushrooms until the liquid they give up has evaporated. Take rice from oven; remove bay leaf and stir in the mushrooms and remaining butter with two pronged fork.',19,'2017-11-08 00:09:27','2017-11-08 00:09:27'),(81,0,'Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Cut the apple into 1/4 inch cubes.',20,'2017-11-08 00:14:59','2017-11-08 00:14:59'),(82,NULL,'Melt 2 T of the butter in an ovenproof saucepan and cook the onion and garlic, stirring, until translucent. Add the rice and stir briefly over low heat until all the grains are coated with butter. Stir in the apple and curry powder.',20,'2017-11-08 00:14:59','2017-11-08 00:14:59'),(83,NULL,'Stir in the broth, and pepper. Add the Tabasco to taste and the bay leaf. Bring mixture just to boil, cover and place in the oven.',20,'2017-11-08 00:14:59','2017-11-08 00:14:59'),(84,NULL,'Bake the rice exactly 17 minutes. Remove the bay leaf and stir in the remaining butter with a two pronged fork. Serve.',20,'2017-11-08 00:14:59','2017-11-08 00:14:59'),(85,0,'Whisk together mustard and vinegar, continue using whisk adding oil slowly; mix-in Beef Maggi; add oregano and pepper; chill before serving.',21,'2017-11-08 00:17:55','2017-11-08 00:17:55'),(86,0,'Whisk together mustard and vinegar; add oil slowly; continue stirring, add port; season with pepper. Chill before serving.',22,'2017-11-08 00:20:09','2017-11-08 00:20:09'),(87,0,'Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Shape into small patties. Cover and fry over low heat in lightly greased skillet for 15 minutes. Remove cover, drain fat and continue frying until brown. Serve 4.',23,'2017-11-08 00:22:25','2017-11-08 00:22:25'),(88,0,'Combine the bourbon, rum and brandy with the sugar in a mixing bowl and let stand three hours or longer. Stir well.',24,'2017-11-08 00:25:55','2017-11-08 00:25:55'),(89,NULL,'Beat the yolks until slightly thickened and pale yellow in color. Pour and scrape them into the sugar mixture. Blend well. Set aside and let stand three hours.',24,'2017-11-08 00:25:55','2017-11-08 00:25:55'),(90,NULL,'Beat the cream until stiff and fold it into the mixture. Place in a bowl and chill. Add a pinch of nutmeg to each cup as served.',24,'2017-11-08 00:25:55','2017-11-08 00:25:55');
